Vintage-style illustration of a writer's desk split diagonally in two contrasting halves: one side shows an antique mahogany writing desk with scattered fountain pens, ink bottles, and cream-colored manuscript pages with visible paragraph indentations; the other side displays a modern workspace with glowing code fragments floating above a sleek keyboard, tangled cables forming intricate patterns like neural pathways. Both sides share a single steaming coffee cup balanced perfectly on the dividing line. The color palette uses warm sepia tones and aged paper textures on the writing side, transitioning to cool electric blues and amber syntax highlighting colors on the coding side. Small origami-like geometric shapes made of folded paper and pixelated fragments drift between both worlds, suggesting the shared complexity beneath seemingly simple building blocks. Dramatic overhead lighting casts long shadows, emphasizing depth and craftsmanship in both disciplines.
